article.description: — Dwight Wilson III had 21 points as Ohio edged past Buffalo 76-75 on Friday night.
article.headline: Wilson scores 21 to carry Ohio over Buffalo 76-75
article.linkText: Wilson scores 21 to carry Ohio over Buffalo 76-75
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- — Dwight Wilson III had 21 points as Ohio edged past Buffalo 76-75 on Friday night. Wilson made 8 of 10 shots, including a layup with 25.7 seconds left to cap the scoring. Ronaldo Segu’s 3-point attempt with less than a second left was off the mark. Ben Roderick had 17 points for Ohio (10-6, 6-4 Mid-American Conference). Jason Preston added 14 points and nine rebounds, and Lunden McDay had 10 points. Jayvon Graves had 18 points and three blocks for the Bulls (6-6, 4-4). Josh Mballa added 14 points and 12 rebounds, and Jeenathan Williams also had 14 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
